<p style="text-align:center;"><strong><span style="text-decoration:underline;font-size:medium;">Internet Options for Families</span></strong></p>
<p>The New Brighton Area School District is dedicated to sharing resources with families to help enhance connectivity.  The following may be options for internet connectivity if you presently do not have home internet service:</p>
<p><strong>Comcast</strong> - Many public hotspots are now free.  Additionally the are providing 2 free months with their Internet Essentials Program <a href="https://www.internetessentials.com/">https://www.internetessentials.com/</a></p>
<p><strong>Verizon</strong> - Announced that many cell phones will now receive the ability to be a free hotspot for connecting other devices.  Check your plan for more details.</p>
<p><strong>AT&amp;T</strong> - Low cost internet option at <a href="https://m.att.com/shopmobile/internet/access/">https://m.att.com/shopmobile/internet/access/</a></p>
<p><strong>Spectrum</strong> - Offering free internet service.  Call (844)-488-8398</p>
<p><strong>Armstrong Cable</strong> - Announced relaxed data limits.  Check plan for details.  </p>
<p><strong>NBASD</strong> - Guest WiFi is available in our bus lanes and parking lots.  Please do not exit vehicles and maintain social distancing, but residents may park on our premises to utilize our NBASD Guest internet.  </p>
